The paper proposes an active learning architecture for robots to learn sequences of motor policies to achieve complex tasks. This involves the use of procedures, which are sequences of policies defined by the combination of previously learned skills. The paper also discusses the use of goal-directed exploration strategies. These topics are all related to robotics and machine learning, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
